  "text": "We selected the Self-Attentive Network for two reasons. First, it shows state-of-the art performance on natural language processing tasks [CITATION_1] . Secondly, it suffers less of the long-memory problem 5 of classic RNNs: in the Self-Attentive case the RNN computes only a local summary of each instruction. Our research hypothesis is that it would behave well over the long sequences of instructions composing binary functions; and this hypothesis is indeed confirmed in our experiments (see Section 6). ",
